    @ModelExternalEvents(imported={SwitchOnIndoorGarden.class,SwitchOffIndoorGarden.class,SwitchLightOnIndoorGarden.class,SwitchLightOffIndoorGarden.class})

public class IndoorGardenElectricityModel
extends fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.hioa.models.AtomicHIOA
implements IndoorGardenOperationI
    The class IndoorGardenElectricityModel implements a simulation model for the electricity consumption of an indoor garden.

    Description

    The indoor garden has three states from the electricity consumption point of vue which are defined by the State enumeration type:

    1. State.OFF: the garden is off and its light is off.
    2. State.LIGHT_ON: the garden is on and its light is on.
    3. State.LIGHT_OFF: the garden is on but its light is off.

    The model imports four event types controlling its mode:

    1. SwitchOnIndoorGarden: when the indoor garden is in state OFF, these events turn it on but with the light off.
    2. SwitchOffIndoorGarden: when the indoor garden is in state LIGHT_ON or LIGHT_OFF, these events turn it off.
    3. SwitchLightOnIndoorGarden: when the indoor garden is in state LIGHT_OFF, these events turn the light on.
    4. SwitchLightOffIndoorGarden: when the indoor garden is in state LIGHT_ON, these events turn the light off.

    White-box Invariant

     invariant       true        // no more invariant

    Black-box Invariant

     invariant       URI != null && !URI.isEmpty()
 invariant       LIGHT_OFF_CONSUMPTION > 0.0
 invariant       LIGHT_ON_CONSUMPTION > LIGHT_OFF_CONSUMPTION
 invariant       TENSION > 0.0
 invariant       getState() != State.OFF || currentIntensity.getValue() == 0.0
 invariant       getState() != State.LIGHT_ON || currentIntensity.getValue() == LIGHT_ON_CONSUMPTION/TENSION
 invariant       getState() != State.LIGHT_OFF || currentIntensity.getValue() == LIGHT_OFF_CONSUMPTION/TENSION
